        "`accesspoint.go` and `wifi.go` similarly expose extensive function-pointer-based injection for each dependency edge, again with minimal policy translation.",
        "This creates a systemic seam pattern where dependency boundaries are verbose but not semantically meaningful."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Create a narrower, intentional runtime contract per subsystem that contains only behavior-meaningful calls (e.g., `ContainerControl`, `SnapshotOps`) and inject concrete collaborators directly; remove no-op adapter layers and replace one-line wrappers with focused facades where behavior actually changes. This should reduce call depth and make seam tests assert intent, not plumbing.",
