    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "main-bootstraps-mixed-responsibility",
      "summary": "Main bootstrap mixes startup orchestration, transport lifecycle, connectivity policy, and host-mode side effects in one flow.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/main.go",
        "goseg/main_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`main.go` combines CLI parsing (`parseStartupOptions`), bootstrap wiring (`bootstrapSubsystems`), HTTP/WS server lifecycle (`startServerWithRuntime`), network recovery policy (`C2cCheckWith`), and kill-switch reboot timing (`killSwitch`) in a single execution path.",
        "`startServerWithRuntime` simultaneously starts both listeners, owns shutdown orchestration, and does cross-server error handling, so changes to one transport concern affect unrelated startup and kill-switch paths.",
        "Tests in `main_test.go` only exercise that callbacks are wired, not that these lifecycle responsibilities are separated into independently testable units."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split startup into explicit collaborators (e.g., `StartupCoordinator`, `ServerLifecycleManager`, `ConnectivitySupervisor`) with dedicated interfaces and data structs; keep `main.go` as composition-only. Move kill-switch logic into a small policy service driven by connectivity snapshots, and keep transport boot logic transport-specific.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "pass-through-seam-overengineering"
